            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the aubergine is nearly ready, add your <strong>cashew nuts</strong>, <strong>coconut flakes </strong>and your <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>diced chilli </strong>to a large piece of <strong>tin foil </strong>with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and mix it all together</p><p>Scrunch the foil around the cashews and coconut to form a tightly sealed parcel and add to the baking tray for 10 min or until the nuts are browned and caramelised</p><p>Once caramelised add the <strong>lime zest </strong>and give everything a good mix up – these are your <strong>spicy zesty nuts</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
